<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a smoking pipe made of the root of the
brier{1}.</def> <note><ex>Brierroot</ex> seems to have been used
formerly as a term meaning root of the <spn>Smilax laurifolia</spn> and
is now defined as root of the <spn>Erica arborea</spn>. Not clear when
this changed. -- PJC.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

